{% comment %}
  ============================================================================
  header.liquid — STATIC VERSION (Step 1 of 2)
  ============================================================================

  WHAT THIS IS:
  Hardcoded HTML that matches the screenshot exactly. Nothing here is dynamic.
  No Liquid variables, no logic tags, no theme settings. Every word you see below
  is plain text typed directly into the file.

  WHY STATIC FIRST:
  So you can see it rendering correctly before anything depends on Shopify
  data (menus, cart, customer accounts). Once you confirm this LOOKS right,
  we swap pieces over to live Liquid one at a time — see "NEXT STEPS" at the
  very bottom of this file.

  4 ROWS, TOP TO BOTTOM:
    1. .header__promo   — navy bar, countdown timer
    2. .header__utility — track order / store finder / help, lang switcher
    3. .header__main    — logo, search bar, sign in, cart
    4. .header__nav     — category links with dropdown carets
  ============================================================================
{% endcomment %}

<header class="header" data-header>

  <!-- ROW 1: PROMO BAR — navy background, countdown on the right -->
  <div class="header__promo">
    <div class="header__promo-inner page-width">
      <span class="header__promo-text">
        🛎️ Hurry! Sale ends in...
      </span>
      <span class="header__promo-timer">
        <span class="header__promo-timer-unit">00D</span>
        <span class="header__promo-timer-sep">:</span>
        <span class="header__promo-timer-unit">11H</span>
        <span class="header__promo-timer-sep">:</span>
        <span class="header__promo-timer-unit">48M</span>
        <span class="header__promo-timer-sep">:</span>
        <span class="header__promo-timer-unit">54S</span>
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROW 2: UTILITY BAR — help links left, language switcher right -->
  <div class="header__utility">
    <div class="header__utility-inner page-width">
      <nav class="header__utility-links" aria-label="Customer service">
        <a href="#" class="header__utility-link">TRACK MY ORDER</a>
        <a href="#" class="header__utility-link">STORE FINDER</a>
        <a href="#" class="header__utility-link">HELP CENTRE</a>
      </nav>

      <button type="button" class="header__lang-switcher">
        <span class="header__lang-flag">🇺🇸</span>
        <span class="header__lang-label">ENGLISH (US)</span>
        <span class="header__lang-caret">▾</span>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROW 3: MAIN BAR — logo, search, sign in, cart -->
  <div class="header__main">
    <div class="header__main-inner page-width">

      <a href="#" class="header__logo">ECOME</a>

      <div class="header__search">
        <input
          type="text"
          class="header__search-input"
          placeholder="What are you looking for?"
        >
        <button type="button" class="header__search-mic" aria-label="Voice search">
          🎤
        </button>
        <button type="button" class="header__search-submit" aria-label="Search">
          🔍
        </button>
      </div>

      <div class="header__main-right">
        <a href="#" class="header__account">
          <span class="header__account-icon">👤</span>
          <span class="header__account-label">Sign in/ Register</span>
        </a>

        <a href="#" class="header__cart">
          <span class="header__cart-icon-wrap">
            🛍️
            <span class="header__cart-badge">1</span>
          </span>
          <span class="header__cart-label">Cart</span>
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROW 4: NAV BAR — category links, some with dropdown carets -->
  <nav class="header__nav" aria-label="Main navigation">
    <div class="header__nav-inner page-width">
      <a href="#" class="header__nav-link header__nav-link--deals">✨ Great deals✨</a>
      <a href="#" class="header__nav-link">"Obsolete"</a>
      <a href="#" class="header__nav-link">Smartphones</a>
      <a href="#" class="header__nav-link header__nav-link--dropdown">Laptops <span class="header__nav-caret">▾</span></a>
      <a href="#" class="header__nav-link header__nav-link--dropdown">Tablets <span class="header__nav-caret">▾</span></a>
      <a href="#" class="header__nav-link header__nav-link--dropdown">Gaming consoles <span class="header__nav-caret">▾</span></a>
      <a href="#" class="header__nav-link">Smartwatches</a>
      <a href="#" class="header__nav-link header__nav-link--dropdown">More <span class="header__nav-caret">▾</span></a>
    </div>
  </nav>

</header>

{% comment %}
  ============================================================================
  NEXT STEPS (do these one at a time, test after each one):

  1. PROMO BAR
     - Replace hardcoded "00D : 11H : 48M : 54S" with a real countdown.
       That needs header.js reading a target end-date and updating the
       4 .header__promo-timer-unit spans every second.
     - Replace hardcoded promo text with a theme setting (section.settings.promo_text)
       so merchants can edit it without touching code.
     - Add an {% if %} to hide the whole row if no promo is set.

  2. UTILITY BAR
     - TRACK MY ORDER / STORE FINDER / HELP CENTRE → real page URLs
       ({{ routes.X }} or {{ pages.X.url }}).
     - Language switcher → swap the static flag/label for Shopify's
       {% form 'localization' %} so it actually changes locale/currency.

  3. MAIN BAR
     - Logo → {{ shop.name | link_to: routes.root_url }} or an uploaded image.
     - Search input → wrap in a real <form action="{{ routes.search_url }}">
       so Enter actually searches. Mic button needs the Web Speech API in
       header.js if you want real voice input (optional — confirm you want
       this before I build it, it's a bigger lift).
     - Sign in/Register → {{ routes.account_url }}, swap text if customer is
       already logged in ({{ customer }}).
     - Cart → {{ routes.cart_url }}, badge number → {{ cart.item_count }},
       hide badge when count is 0 (same pattern as the version we built earlier).

  4. NAV BAR
     - Replace all 8 hardcoded links with a real Shopify menu loop
       ({% for link in section.settings.menu.links %}), same pattern as
       before. Dropdown carets need real submenus (link.links) plus
       header.js hover/click logic to show them.
     - "Great deals" and "Obsolete" styling (color, quotes, sparkles) will
       need to either be hardcoded exceptions by handle, or just accepted
       as plain menu items without the special styling once it's dynamic.

  5. MOBILE
     - None of this has a mobile/responsive version yet. Screenshot is
       desktop-only. Tell me what the mobile version should collapse into
       (hamburger menu? which rows stay visible?) before I build it.

  Confirm row 1 + row 3 look right first — those are the highest-risk rows
  (timer, search, cart) — before I wire any of this to real Liquid data.
  ============================================================================
{% endcomment %}